editorialSummary.text: Funky, counter-service cafe offering slices, salads, Italian entrees & house-bottled lemonade.

originalText.text: had the chicken vodka pizza and chicken bacon ranch. both were so nice and crispy and reminded me of how much better a good NYC slice is. highly recommend Calabria!

originalText.text: Found by a chance, well worth popping in when in the area. Really tasty pizza with friendly service. Place seems to be popular with local police personnel too which should be good indication of the quality food.

originalText.text:
Ive been here several times and spend a lot of money here food is good! Especially the salad but Terrible customer service this time I walked in being challenged by one of the employees! The employee was going back and forth with me rudely about what I didn’t order previously to coming which I wanted again and that was a small side Greek salad that I ordered several times  along with other items… he was consistently saying rudely that hasn’t been done in two years and I  let him know that I recently brought it there was no issue I don’t understand why I’m getting this response now, being that he wasn’t the the one that did the side salad but the owner did he wanted to continuously argue me down about it! I told him several times the conversation was over it’s okay I know what I ordered just say it’s no longer available and move on with my new order. He didn’t and kept speaking on the side salad…so I proceeded to leave not getting my money and being treated rudely! As I’m leaving he said “don’t ever come back here again” I told him your Boss won’t be too please with you being rude to customers and also losing business b/c you couldn’t control your ego! I told him you  don’t ever have to worry about me coming into this place again this isn’t the only place to eat to be mindful of that when you decide to allow your ego to overpower you! I’m one person imagine him being rude to several others! LOSING BUSINESS to customers that frequently go to your store isn’t a good look!
Sorry to the owner but your workers differently need an attitude adjustment and thank you for the service I did receive and I enjoyed the salads but I can no longer give this place business.

(Service 2 stars b/c of what happens) other then that several of the employees are welcoming and accommodating.

Update: thanks for the reply…I didn’t go into the establishment but I did have someone order me a salad yesterday 9/7/23. My review wasn’t to bring down the business but to bring awareness to how one of you customers was treated which was me. I never experienced that before going there so it was major shock…. I love the salad and other things…so just for recognizing my review and replying respectfully I appreciate that. I always recommend this place for a salad even if I’m not ordering.

Thank You!

originalText.text: Me and my friend order medium Calabria pizza and it was absolutely amazing. It has 6 enormous slices of pizza (25$). Two of us ate 2 (1,5 slices) and it was AMAZING! Pizza was done in 10 minutes. You can choose from many options (veggie, meat, plain cheese). I recommend this place highly! They are really nice people working there and they make pizza in front of you. You can also buy slice of pizza. All the best!
